.TH "__pci_read_base" 9 "__pci_read_base" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__pci_read_base \- Read a PCI BAR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __pci_read_base
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "enum pci_bar_type type "  ","
.BI "struct resource *res "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pos "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the PCI device
.IP "type" 12
type of the BAR
.IP "res" 12
resource buffer to be filled in
.IP "pos" 12
BAR position in the config space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 1 if the BAR is 64-bit, or 0 if 32-bit.
